def dist(a, b, ax=1):
    return np.linalg.norm(a - b, axis=ax)

In [9]:
# To store the value of centroids when it updates
C_old = np.zeros(C.shape)
# Cluster Lables(0, 1, 2)
clusters = np.zeros(len(X))
# Error func. - Distance between new centroids and old centroids
error = dist(C, C_old, None)
#print(error)
# Loop will run till the error becomes zero
while error != 0:
    # Assigning each value to its closest cluster
    for i in range(len(X)):
        distances = dist(X[i], C)
        cluster = np.argmin(distances)
        clusters[i] = cluster
    # Storing the old centroid values
    C_old = deepcopy(C)
    # Finding the new centroids by taking the average value
    for i in range(k):
        points = [X[j] for j in range(len(X)) if clusters[j] == i]
        C[i] = np.mean(points, axis=0)
    error = dist(C, C_old, None)

    diff1=[]
    for j in range(802):
        D1 = np.linalg.norm(C[i]-diff[j])

    min_ind = 0

        if(diff1[j]<diff1[min_ind]):
            min_ind = j
    C_ind.append(min_ind)

#Assigning "Win" or "Lose" label to all pokemon after battle simulation with all the centroid pokemon of the clusters
mtype = ["Physical","Special","Status"]
WL=[]
types=['Normal','Fire','Water','Electric','Grass','Ice','Fighting','Poison','Ground','Flying','Psychic','Bug','Rock','Ghost','Dragon','Dark','Steel','Fairy']
for i in range(802):
    W=[]
    for k in range(len(C)):
        h1=d1.iloc[i,4]
        h2=d1.iloc[C_ind[k],4]
        while h1!=0 or h2!=0:
            #Pokemon 1
            p=np.random.choice(2)
            dt1=d1.iloc[C_ind[k],2]
            dt2=d1.iloc[C_ind[k],3]
            for j in range(dt.shape[0]):
                if dt.iloc[j,0]==dt1 and dt.iloc[j,1]==dt2:
                    r1=j
            col1 = d1.iloc[i,2+p]
            while (col1=="Null"):
                p=np.random.choice(2)
                col1 = d1.iloc[i,2+p]
            c1=mtype[np.random.choice(3)]
            tind1 = types.index(col1)
            if c1=='Physical':
                del1=dt.iloc[r1,2+tind1]*(d1.iloc[i,5]-C[k][1])
                if del1>h2:
                    h2=0
                elif del1<=h2 and del1>0:
                    h2=h2-del1
                else:
                    h2=h2
            elif c1=='Special':
                del1=dt.iloc[r1,2+tind1]*(d1.iloc[i,7]-C[k][3])
                if del1>h2:
                    h2=0
                elif del1<=h2 and del1>0:
                    h2=h2-del1
                else:
                    h2=h2
            else:
                del1=np.random.choice(4)
                h2=h2-1
            #Checking health of 2nd pokemon
            if h2==0:
                W.append("Win")
                break
            #Pokemon 2
            p=np.random.choice(2)
            dt1=d1.iloc[i,2]
            dt2=d1.iloc[i,3]
            for j in range(dt.shape[0]):
                if dt.iloc[j,0]==dt1 and dt.iloc[j,1]==dt2:
                    r2=j    
            col2=d1.iloc[C_ind[k],2+p]
            while (col2 == "Null"):
                p=np.random.choice(2)
                col2=d1.iloc[C_ind[k],2+p]
            c2=mtype[np.random.choice(3)]
            tind2=types.index(col2)
            if c2=='Physical':
                del2=dt.iloc[r2,2+tind2]*(C[k][0]-d1.iloc[i,6])
                if del2>h1:
                    h1=0
                elif del2<=h1 and del2>0:
                    h1=h1-del2
                else:
                    h1=h1
            elif c2=='Special':
                del2=dt.iloc[r2,2+tind2]*(C[k][2]-d1.iloc[i,8])
                if del2>h1:
                    h1=0
                elif del2<=h1 and del2>0:
                    h1=h1-del2
                else:
                    h1=h1
            else:
                del2=np.random.choice(4)
                h1=h1-1
            #Checking health of 1st pokemon
            if h1==0:
                W.append("Lose")
                break
    if (W.count("Win")>W.count("Lose")):
        WL.append("Win")
    elif (W.count("Win")<W.count("Lose")):
        WL.append("Lose")
    else:
        WL.append("Draw")

count1=0
moves=[]
power=[]
index1=[]
while(count1!=4):
    m1=np.random.choice(dm.shape[0])
    if(d1.iloc[i1-1,2]==dm.iloc[m1-1,3] or d1.iloc[i1-1,3]==dm.iloc[m1-1,3]):
        if(dm.iloc[m1-1,1] not in moves):
            moves.append(dm.iloc[m1-1,1])
            power.append(int(dm.iloc[m1-1,5]))
            index1.append(m1)
            count1=count1+1;

#battle simulation based on move type effectiveness and pokemon stats data
#Since battle outcome depends on pokemon stats, pokemon of the same cluster are assumed to be more effective against each other
h1=d1.iloc[i1-1,4]
h2=d1.iloc[i2-1,4]
types=['Normal','Fire','Water','Electric','Grass','Ice','Fighting','Poison','Ground','Flying','Psychic','Bug','Rock','Ghost','Dragon','Dark','Steel','Fairy']
XX1=[]
XX2=[]
while h1!=0 or h2!=0:
    #Pokemon 1
    p=np.random.choice(4)
    move1=moves[p]
    p1=power[p]
    x=index1[p]
    t1=dm.iloc[x-1,3]
    c1=dm.iloc[x-1,4]
    dt1=d1.iloc[i2-1,2]
    dt2=d1.iloc[i2-1,3]
    for i in range(dt.shape[0]):
        if dt.iloc[i,0]==dt1 and dt.iloc[i,1]==dt2:
            r1=i
    col1=types.index(dm.iloc[x-1,3])
    if c1=='Physical':
        del1=dt.iloc[r1,2+col1]*(max(p1,a1[0])-a2[1])
        if del1>h2:
            h2=0
        elif del1<=h2 and del1>0:
            h2=h2-del1
        else:
            h2=h2
    elif c1=='Special':
        del1=dt.iloc[r1,2+col1]*(max(p1,a1[2])-a2[3])
        if del1>h2:
            h2=0
        elif del1<=h2 and del1>0:
            h2=h2-del1
        else:
            h2=h2
    else:
        del1=np.random.choice(5)
        a2[del1]=a2[del1]-1
    XX1.append(move1)
    #Checking health of 2nd pokemon
    if h2==0:
        print(d1.iloc[i1-1,1],' wins!!')
        break
    #Pokemon 2
    p=np.random.choice(4)
    move2=moves1[p]
    p2=power1[p]
    x=index2[p]
    t2=dm.iloc[x-1,3]
    c2=dm.iloc[x-1,4]
    dt1=d1.iloc[i1-1,2]
    dt2=d1.iloc[i1-1,3]
    for i in range(dt.shape[0]):
        if dt.iloc[i,0]==dt1 and dt.iloc[i,1]==dt2:
            r2=i
    col2=types.index(dm.iloc[x-1,3])
    if c2=='Physical':
        del2=dt.iloc[r2,2+col2]*(max(p2,a2[0])-a1[1])
        if del2>h1:
            h1=0
        elif del2<=h1 and del2>0:
            h1=h1-del2
        else:
            h1=h1
    elif c2=='Special':
        del2=dt.iloc[r2,2+col2]*(max(p2,a2[2])-a1[3])
        if del2>h1:
            h1=0
        elif del2<=h1 and del2>0:
            h1=h1-del2
        else:
            h1=h1
    else:
        del2=np.random.choice(5)
        a1[del2]=a1[del2]-1
    XX2.append(move2)
    #Checking health of 1st pokemon
    if h1==0:
        print(d1.iloc[i2-1,1],' wins!!')
        break
